==Current scene==
===Regular events===
*'''Magyar K<U+00E9>preg<U+00E9>ny Fesztiv<U+00E1>l - Hungarian Comics Festival'''. Annual event every spring, organized by the Hungarian Comic Publishers' Association. The event's main focus is on the programs (debates, meeting artists, presentations, movies, etc).

*'''K<U+00E9>preg<U+00E9>ny B<U+00F6>rze <U+2013> Comics Exchange Market'''. (In some European countries they're translated to ComiCons, although US Cons are somewhat different) Twice a year (spring and fall). The first was held in 2001. The most fan oriented event.

*'''Hungarocomix'''. A fair showcasing the publishers<U+2019> yearly work. Usually a few weeks before Christmas. The most publisher oriented event.

*'''K<U+00E9>preg<U+00E9>ny Kedvel<U+0151>k Klubja''' (KKK in short) <U+2013> '''Comics Fans<U+2019> Club'''. Every last Thursday of the month. They are usually held in kArton gal<U+00E9>ria or on the terrace of Kultiplex. Every month a theme is discussed with guests. The "club" is open to all people, but usually most of the audience consists of veteran fans and professionals.

===Shops===
Comics are likely to be found in book stores. There's a large variety of children comics in newspaper shops. Comic book stores are rare, but some exist in the capitol. Hungarian creations are usually printed in small numbers and sold in a loose alternative network.
*Trillian (Specializing in current American and Manga titles)
*Comicsinvest (Webshop specializing in American and Manga back issues)
*Edu<U+00E1>rd (Specializing in Hungarian titles and back issues)
*King Comics (closed in 2007)

===Organizations===
*MKSz - Magyar K<U+00E9>preg<U+00E9>nykiad<U+00F3>k Sz<U+00F6>vets<U+00E9>ge / Hungarian Comics Publishers' Association [http://www.kepregeny.info | official website]
*MKA - Magyar K<U+00E9>preg<U+00E9>ny Akad<U+00E9>mia / Hungarian Comic Publishers<U+2019> Association [http://kepregenyakademia.hu/ | official website]
*kArton gal<U+00E9>ria / kArton Galery [http://www.karton.hu | official website]

==Famous or important comic book artists, publishers, editors with Hungarian roots==
''Note: the following list contains people, who have/had Hungarian heritage, although were not involved directly in the Hungarian comics scene. This list is to be regarded as trivia.''  
* [[Joseph Pulitzer]] Hungarian immigrant, born in Mak<U+00F3>.
* [[Alex Toth]] Son of Hungarian immigrants. Many interviews and colleague's memoirs reflect, that he remained intact with his (parent's) cultural background.<ref>[http://www.tothfans.com/adisplay.php?a=375 tothfans.com Alex Toth's Biography. The Official Alex Toth Website]</ref><ref>[http://www.tothfans.com/adisplay.php?a=365 tothfans.com  Remembering Alex Toth. The Official Alex Toth Website]</ref><ref>"Burbank was a renovated and renewed city, and in Belmont Village he found other Hungarians, heard the folk songs and stories he hadn't heard and longed for through decades" - http://www.tothfans.com/adisplay.php?a=359</ref>
* [[Paul Gulacy]]
* [[Paul Winkler]] Born in Budapest. He was the first to establish Disney comics in France, which happened to be the start of French comic books.<ref>[http://legends.disney.go.com/legends/detail?key=Paul+Winkler Disney Legends - Paul Winkler]</ref>
* [[Marcel Gotlib]]
* [[Miriam Katin]] Born in Budapest, emigrated in 1957.
* [[Rick Magyar]] American Comic Book artist.

